-vis%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20religion%20and%20equality%20of%20status%2C%20persons%20like%20the%20petitioner%20who%20belong%20to%20the%20marginalised%20society%20are%20prevented%20from%20even%20offering%20prayers%20to%20the%20God%20almighty%20who%20belongs%20to%20all%20of%20us%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20said%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2Fmmathimuruganvhrce-480545.pdf%5C%22%3EApril%2019%20order%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENoting%20that%20Murugan%20as%20well%20as%20members%20of%20his%20community%20were%20denied%20entry%20into%20the%20Arulmighu%20Shri%20Mangala%20Nayaki%20Amman%20Temple%20by%20persons%20who%20claimed%20to%20be%20superior%20to%20Murugan%E2%80%99s%20community%20by%20virtue%20of%20their%20birth%2C%20the%20bench%20also%20said%20it%20could%20not%20remain%20aloof%20to%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20court%20cannot%20be%20a%20mute%20spectator%20and%20permit%20perpetuation%20of%20the%20practice%20of%20untouchability.%20Therefore%2C%20this%20writ%20petition%20is%20disposed%20of%20giving%20direction%20to%20the%20second%20respondent%20to%20ensure%20compliance%20of%20the%20decision%20arrived%20at%20in%20the%20peace%20committee%20meeting%20held%20on%20December%2013%2C%202021%20between%20the%20two%20parties%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPudukkottai%E2%80%99s%20then-district%20collector%20Kavitha%20Ramu%20was%20named%20as%20the%20second%20respondent%20in%20the%20case.%20She%20has%20since%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftamil.oneindia.com%2Fnews%2Ftamilnadu%2Fpudukkottai-collector-kavita-ramu-transferred-to-cmda-transfer-of-ias-officers-full-list-512083.html%5C%22%3Ereplaced%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpudukkottai.nic.in%5C%22%3EI.S.%20Mercy%20Ramya%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barandbench.com%2Fnews%2Flitigation%2Fmadras-high-court-temple-scheduled-caste-worship%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBar%20and%20Bench%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20peace%20committee%20meeting%20involved%20an%20agreement%20among%20Mangalanadu%E2%80%99s%20residents%20that%20Scheduled%20Caste%20villagers%20will%20be%20allowed%20to%20access%20the%20temple%20and%20partake%20in%20its%20festivities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20high%20court%20bench%20recognised%20that%20the%20meeting%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20legal%20force%2C%20but%20directed%20those%20who%20allegedly%20obstructed%20Murugan%E2%80%99s%20entry%20into%20the%20temple%20to%20adhere%20to%20the%20meeting%E2%80%99s%20agreements%20because%20they%20participated%20in%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20no%20doubt%20true%20that%20there%20is%20no%20legal%20force%20to%20the%20peace%20committee%20meeting%2C%20but%20having%20participated%20in%20the%20same%2C%20they%20are%20bound%20by%20the%20decision%20taken%20therein%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20order%20read.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20order%20continued%20to%20say%20that%20the%20incident%20represented%20an%20%E2%80%9Caffront%20to%20the%20very%20social%20fibre%20guaranteed%20by%20the%20constitution%E2%80%9D%20and%20directed%20the%20police%20to%20invoke%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Facts_states%2Ftamil-nadu%2F1982%2F1982TN14.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ETamil%20Nadu%20Prevention%20of%20Dangerous%20Activities%20Act%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20against%20anyone%20who%20indulges%20in%20similar%20acts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EVengaivayal%20incident%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPudukkottai%20district%20is%20also%20home%20to%20Vengaivayal%20village%2C%20which%20is%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20another%20recent%20caste-based%20injustice.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20December%202022%2C%20a