0G.%20Vaishakan%E2%80%99s%20phone%20was%20seized%20by%20the%20police%20while%C2%A0investigating%20a%20case%20involving%20Shajan%20Skaria%2C%20the%20editor%20of%20%3Cem%3EMarunadan%20Malayali%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FKochi%2Fkerala-high-court-criticises-police-for-seizing-mobile-phone-of-journalist%2Farticle67063858.ece%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVaishakan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fnational%2Fsouth%2Fprotest-brewing-in-kerala-over-mlas-threat-to-media-police-action-against-journalists-1235838.html%5C%22%3Emoved%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Kerala%20high%20court%20which%20questioned%20the%20police%E2%80%99s%20rationale%20behind%20the%20seizure%20when%20the%20journalist%20was%20neither%20a%20suspect%20nor%20an%20accused%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20orally%20observed%20that%20it%20was%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20the%20journalist%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%20The%20court%20said%20that%20if%20the%20phone%E2%80%99s%20seizure%20is%20necessary%20for%20an%20investigation%20then%20there%20are%20procedures%20in%20place%20before%20the%20police%20can%20seize%20them.%20A%20journalist%20is%20%E2%80%9Cpart%20of%20the%20fourth%20estate%20and%20may%20be%20getting%20several%20pieces%20of%20information%20on%20his%20phone%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimply%20because%20a%20journalist%20has%20got%20some%20information%20about%20a%20crime%2C%20his%2Fher%20mobile%20cannot%20be%20seized%20without%20following%20the%20procedures%20under%20the%20CrPC.%20Such%20actions%20of%20the%20police%20would%20create%20a%20bad%20precedent%2C%20the%20court%20added%20according%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKerala%20police%20was%20also%20reportedly%20criticised%20for%20its%20heavy%20handedness%20in%20the%20case%20from%20different%20quarters%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said.%20The%20state%20police%20had%20seized%20all%20computers%20and%20other%20gadgets%20of%20the%20online%20media%20publication%20and%20carried%20out%20raids%20at%20the%20staff%E2%80%99s%20houses%20as%20part%20of%20their%20search%20for%20Skaria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESkaria%20was%20accused%20of%20allegedly%20spreading%20misinformation%20and%20intentional%20defamation%20by%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%20CPI(M)%20MLA%20PV%20Sreenijan.%20The%20Kerala%20police%20have%20filed%20a%20case%20under%20the%20SC%2FST%20(Prevention%20of%20Atrocities)%20Act%20based%20on%20the%20MLA%E2%80%99s%20petition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Monday%20gave%20Skaria%20interim%20protection%20from%20arrest%20after%20the%20Kerala%20high%20court%20rejected%20his%20bail%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20left-front%20MLA%20PV%20Anwar%20is%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fnational%2Fsouth%2Fprotest-brewing-in-kerala-over-mlas-threat-to-media-police-action-against-journalists-1235838.html%5C%22%3Efacing%20criticism%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20threatening%20a%20section%20of%20online%20media%20for%20publishing%20reports%20that%20were%20critical%20of%20him.%20The%20MLA%2C%20who%20is%20reportedly%20often%20embroiled%20in%20controversies%20surrounding%20his%20business%20ventures%2C%20had%20threatened%20leading%20journalists%20from%20Malayalam%20news%20channels%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposition%20leader%20VD%20Satheesan%20on%20Monday%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fnational%2Fsouth%2Fprotest-brewing-in-kerala-over-mlas-threat-to-media-police-action-against-journalists-1235838.html%5C%22%3Easked%3C%2Fa%3E%20whether%20Anwar%20was%20threatening%20the%20media%20with%20the%20blessings%20of%20the%20left-front%20government%20in%20Kerala%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Thiruvananthapuram%20Press%20Club%20staged%20a%20protest%20march%20in%20front%20of%20the%20government%20secretariat%20seeking%20action%20against%20Anwar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kerala%20police%20is%20also%20under%20fire%20for%20registering%20cases%20against%20the%20reporters%20of%20two%20leading%20Malayalam%20news%20channels%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689068304000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F18192032%2Fpinarayi-vijayan.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fkerala-hc-slams-police-for-action-against-journalist-says-fundamental-rights-violated%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Thiruvananthapuram%20Press%20Club%20staged%20a%20protest%20march%20in%20front%20of%20the%20government%20secretariat%20on%20Monday%20criticising%20the%20infringement%20of%20press%20freedoms%20in%20the%20state.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fkerala-hc-slams-police-for-action-against-journalist-says-fundamental-rights-violated%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NATO%20head%20sees%20'strong%20message'%20on%20Ukraine's%20membership%20bid%20at%20summit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689067725000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-101665409%2Cimgsize-22838.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fnato-head-sees-strong-message-on-ukraines-membership-bid-at-summit%2Farticleshow%2F101665421.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F101665421.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%20NATO%20Secretary%20General%20Jens%20Stoltenberg%20said%20Ukraine%20would%20get%20a%20%26quot%3Bpositive%20and%20strong%20message%26quot%3B%20on%20its%20path%20to%20membership%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20as%20leaders%20of%20the%20Western%20military%20alliance%20meet%20to%20discuss%20the%20fallout%20from%20Russia's%20invasion%20that%20brought%20war%20to%20their%20doorstep.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fnato-head-sees-strong-message-on-ukraines-membership-bid-at-summit%2Farticleshow%2F101665421.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fnato-head-sees-strong-message-on-ukraines-membership-bid-at-summit%2Famp_articleshow%2F101665421.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fnato-head-sees-strong-message-on-ukraines-membership-bid-at-summit%2Famp_articleshow%2F101665421.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Invalid'%3A%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Govt's%20Extensions%20to%20ED%20Chief%20S.K.%20Mishra%20After%20Its%202021%20Order%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F11%2F15174623%2FSKMishra_EDdirector_141120_1200.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20held%20the%20extensions%20given%20to%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20chief%20S.K.%20Mishra%20after%20its%20own%20order%20barring%20further%20extensions%20as%20invalid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20three-judge%20bench%20of%20Justices%20B.R.%20Gavai%2C%20Vikram%20Nath%20and%20Sanjay%20Karol%2C%20however%2C%20allowed%20Mishra%20to%20continue%20in%20his%20post%20till%20July%2031%2C%202023%2C%20considering%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fenforcement-directorate-sanjay-mishra-supreme-court-fatf%5C%22%3Esaid%20that%20the%20international%20terror%20financing%20watchdog%20FATF%E2%80%99s%20peer%20review%20process%20can%20be%20best%20overseen%20by%20Mishra%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20when%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20had%20told%20the%20apex%20court%20that%20FATF%E2%80%99s%20once-in-a-decade%20peer%20review%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20performance%20in%20curbing%20terror%20financing%20necessitated%20Mishra%E2%80%99s%20extension%2C%20Justice%20Gavai%20had%20asked%20if%20there%20was%20no%20other%20person%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Centire%20organisation%20competent%20to%20discharge%20these%20responsibilities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEven%20if%20we%20accepted%20your%20argument%2C%20what%20will%20happen%20beyond%202023%20when%20Mishra%20finally%20retires%3F%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Gavai%20had%20further%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMishra%20was%20first%20appointed%20the%20director%20of%20the%20ED%20for%20two%20years%20on%20November%2019%2C%202018.%20Later%2C%20by%20an%20order%20dated%20November%2013%2C%202020%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20modified%20the%20appointment%20letter%20retrospectively%20and%20his%20two-year%20term%20was%20changed%20to%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202021%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20of%20Justice%20L.%20Nageswara%20Rao%20upheld%20the%20extension%2C%20saying%20that%20such%20retroactive%20revisions%20are%20only%20allowed%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Crarest%20of%20rare%20cases%E2%80%9D%20but%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsk-mishra-enforcement-directorate-supreme-court-extension%5C%22%3Eno%20further%20extension%20can%20be%20given%20to%20Mishra%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ordered%20no%20further%20extensions%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20issued%20a%20notification%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20a%20second%20extension%20for%20Mishra%20from%20November%2017%2C%202021%20to%20November%2017%2C%202022.%20When%20Congress%20leader%20Jaya%20Thakur%20moved%20court%20against%20this%2C%20the%20government%20gave%20him%20a%20third%20extension%2C%20till%20November%2018%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20government%20promulgated%20an%20ordinance%20last%20year%20under%20which%20the%20tenure%20of%20ED%20and%20CBI%20chiefs%20could%20be%20extended%20by%20up%20to%20three%20years%20after%20the%20mandated%20term%20of%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20amendment%20to%20the%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%20Act%20was%20also%20challenged%20afresh%20in%20the%20apex%20court%20in%20the%20batch%20of%20petitions%2C%20including%20those%20filed%20by%20Congress%20leaders%20Randeep%20Singh%20Surjewala%20and%20Jaya%20Thakur%2C%20and%20Trinamool%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Mahua%20Moitra%20and%20Saket%20Gokhale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-sc-enforcement-directorate-director-sanjay-kumar-mishra-central-vigilance-commission-amendment-act-232449%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20apex%20court%20has%20upheld%20the%20above%20amendments%20made%20to%20the%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%20Act%20and%20the%20Delhi%20Special%20Police%20Establishment%20Act%2C%20asking%20for%20sufficient%20safeguards%20nonetheless.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20noted%20that%20the%20scope%20of%20judicial%20review%20over%20legislation%20is%20very%20limited.%20%E2%80%9CExtension%20can%20be%20granted%20to%20high-level%20officials%20in%20the%20public%20interest%20and%20with%20reasons%20in%20writing%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20the%20court%20held%20that%20the%20extensions%20were%20clearly%20in%20the%20teeth%20of%20its%20%3Cem%3ECommon%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ECause%3C%2Fem%3E%20judgment.%20%E2%80%9CAlthough%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20judgment%20can%20be%20taken%20away%2C%20the%20legislature%20cannot%20annul%20the%20specific%20mandamus%20that%20barred%20further%20extension%E2%80%A6That%20would%20amount%20to%20sitting%20in%20appeal%20over%20judicial%20act%E2%80%9D%2C%20Justice%20Gavai%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThus%2C%20extensions%20given%20after%20verdict%20was%20invalid