ia.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F333977488_871767980572765_2644368810472386431_n_11zon-1688128610-150x200.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-322328%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EJeeth%20Roche%2C%20an%20environmentalist%20and%20founder%20of%20Mangalore%20Green%20Brigade%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Jeeth%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhat%20is%20the%20Miyawaki%20method%20of%20growing%20forests%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAkira%20Miyawaki%2C%20a%20famed%20and%20globally%20acclaimed%20Japanese%20botanist%20came%20up%20with%20a%20method%20of%20growing%20lush%20thriving%20forests%20in%20areas%20of%20land%20where%20not%20a%20single%20tree%20had%20ever%20existed.%20The%20question%20perplexed%20many%20botanists%20as%20to%20how%20it%20was%20possible.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMiyawaki%E2%80%99s%20technique%2C%20which%20first%20came%20up%20around%20the%201950s%2C%20held%20the%20answers.%20As%20he%20explained%20in%20his%20research%2C%20it%20was%20all%20about%20phytosociology%20or%20how%20plant%20species%20interact%20with%20each%20other.%20Every%20piece%20of%20soil%2C%20he%20said%2C%20was%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F263797%2Frajasthan-miyawaki-forest-how-to-grow-dry-land-farmer-increase-income%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etime%20capsule%20of%20a%20forest%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20grow%20a%20forest%20through%20the%20Miyawaki%20method%2C%20one%20needs%20to%20follow%20a%20series%20of%20steps.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20soil%20of%20the%20potential%20forest%20is%20analysed%20and%20enhanced%20with%20the%20addition%20of%20rice%20husk.%20Following%20this%2C%20the%20seedlings%20of%20local%20trees%2C%20herbs%20and%20shrubs%20are%20planted%20randomly%20in%20this%20soil%20and%20in%20close%20clusters%20such%20as%2030%2C000%20per%20hectare.%20The%20next%20three%20years%20that%20follow%20are%20crucial%20as%20the%20area%20is%20monitored%20and%20weeded%20frequently.%20Due%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F259236%2Ffood-forests-george-remedios-mumbai-pune-green-turning-tide%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edensity%20of%20the%20trees%3C%2Fa%3E%20(compared%20to%201%2C000%20per%20hectare%20in%20a%20commercial%20forest)%2C%20the%20trees%20begin%20to%20compete%20for%20resources%20and%20this%20encourages%20faster%20growth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20forest%20begins%20to%20thrive%20and%20is%20then%20left%20to%20grow%20naturally.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Mangaluru%2C%20Jeeth%20has%20been%20successful%20in%20introducing%20the%20Miyawaki%20concept%20along%20the%20National%20Highway%20and%20in%20areas%20like%20Nanthoor%2C%20Gurupura%2C%20the%20Karnataka%20Polytechnic%20College%20and%20Nandigudda.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20how%20he%20did%20it%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20chose%20170%20varieties%20and%20species%20of%20trees%2C%20herbs%20and%20shrubs.%20My%20intention%20was%20to%20grow%20food%20forests%20using%20the%20Miyawaki%20method.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F255198%2Fodisha-women-tribal-system-kodarapalli-thengapalli-forest-protection-environment-natural-resources-over-exploitation-guard-conservation-him16%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThese%20forests%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20be%20open%20for%20all%20species%20to%20thrive.%20Birds%20now%20come%20to%20nest%20in%20the%20trees%20here%20and%20enjoy%20the%20fruits.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJeeth%20says%20he%20is%20far%20from%20finished%20in%20his%20endeavours%2C%20and%20that%20there%20is%20one%20thing%20that%20has%20kept%20him%20going%20and%20always%20will.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20joy%20of%20working%20with%20nature%20is%20a%20great%20experience.%20Nature%20has%20never